1
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,160
Compile the statistics of

2
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:53,759
all ammunition consumption

3
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:55,240
and replenishment since the war began.

4
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,440
I need to report it to the theater commander.

5
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:57,240
Yes, sir.

6
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:57,920
Send today's combat report

7
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:58,979
to my office later.

8
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:00,680
Also send a copy to Commander Liao.

9
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:01,440
Yes, sir.

10
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:23,840
You're still alive.

11
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:25,840
Alive.

12
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,000
One star,

13
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:47,800
Army Chief of Staff,

14
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,800
Major General.

15
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:50,440
Not bad.

16
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,000
Deserter.

17
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:09,560
You stole my sweet potato and ate my noodles.

18
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:11,720
Zhang Yunkui, you're pretty bold.

19
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:14,000
Do you also think I'm a deserter?

20
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,079
Ordered to retreat.

21
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:18,810
Ordered to defend to the death.

22
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:21,040
Every step I took on the Songhu battlefield

23
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,960
was explicitly instructed by the higher-ups.

24
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:25,760
You knew it clearly at the division headquarters.

25
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:26,960
I left Baijiazhai

26
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,840
to meet up with reinforcements in Liuzhen.

27
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:31,640
But the reinforcements withdrew.

28
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,440
Later, we ran into the Japanese.

29
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,320
They surrounded me.

30
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,760
We fought until we ran out of ammunition and supplies,

31
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,120
and the whole army was wiped out.

32
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,880
How did I become a deserter?

33
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:45,760
Lu Yun.

34
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:51,240
We

35
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,680
were classmates at the military academy.

36
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,409
Fought together for ten years,

37
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,720
and have been close friends for ten years.

38
00:04:57,720 --> 00:05:00,200
You know better than anyone what kind of person I am.

39
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,320
Others might mistakenly think

40
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:02,040
that I'm a deserter,

41
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:02,840
a coward.

42
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:04,720
But you can't.

43
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,650
Then what are you doing here today?

44
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,760
The Japanese army is now advancing south and north,

45
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:10,820
besieging Xuzhou.

46
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,440
Our army shoulders the heavy responsibility of reinforcing them.

47
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:14,000
Commander Sun's life and safety

48
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,330
cannot be compromised.

49
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:16,360
I'm not looking for him.

50
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:17,400
Then who are you looking for?

51
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,080
You.

52
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,560
What do you want from me?

53
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,040
I have to get justice

54
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,440
for my 6,000 brothers.

55
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,740
Now is not the time.

56
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,520
Then when is the time?

57
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:30,680
When you brand these 6,000 martyrs

58
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,200
as deserters,

59
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,130
is that the time?

60
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,720
Chief of Staff Lu, I want to ask you,

61
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,240
if it were you,

62
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:40,159
rescued from a pile of dead bodies,

63
00:05:40,159 --> 00:05:41,159
finding yourself

64
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,560
and these brothers

65
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,800
branded as eternal sinners,

66
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,159
what would you do?

67
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,680
Would you still wait for a good time?

68
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:51,480
Would you still look for a good time?

69
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,340
Chief of Staff.

70
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,280
The document.

71
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,080
Stand guard at the door.

72
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,120
Don't let anyone in.

73
00:05:59,120 --> 00:05:59,960
Yes, sir.

74
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,920
I want evidence.

75
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,760
Prove that before the 87th Brigade fell,

76
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:12,680
the division headquarters had already issued an order to retreat.

77
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,080
I want you to find this order.

78
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:14,810
Impossible.

79
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,120
Why?

80
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:23,280
You're afraid of betraying your superior,

81
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:25,810
but not afraid of betraying your conscience.

82
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:27,960
Zhang Yunkui.

83
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:29,840
The dead are gone.

84
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:32,000
The living must consider the big picture.

85
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,520
You're telling me this?

86
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,840
These days, I hid my identity

87
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,200
and joined the Sichuan Army.

88
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:40,860
They marched thousands of miles out of Sichuan.

89
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,440
You have no idea how poorly equipped

90
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:43,640
the local troops are.

91
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,760
You don't know what they wear

92
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:46,720
on their feet.

93
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,320
In the dead of winter,

94
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:49,960
they wear straw sandals.

95
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,140
They have no padded coats,

96
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,520
only unlined garments.

97
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:54,159
What if they are hungry?

98
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:55,490
There's nothing to eat.

99
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,680
With at most five bullets each,

100
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,800
how can they fight this war?

101
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:01,680
They rely on conscience and sheer courage.

102
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,040
Now look at you.

103
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,420
An elite with a star on your shoulder,

104
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,000
wearing a crisp uniform,

105
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,640
in such a warm room,

106
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:10,720
warming up by the stove,

107
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:11,880
and eating roasted sweet potatoes.

108
00:07:11,880 --> 00:07:13,160
Do you really believe we can win

109
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,200
this war?

110
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,280
Can we?

111
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:18,640
If our brothers who go to the battlefield

112
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:19,680
are called deserters,

113
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,160
where is your conscience?

114
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,320
Lu Yun.

115
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:24,180
I'm not doing this for myself.

116
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:25,920
I'm doing this for what you also

117
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,520
believe in your heart.

118
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,480
Yunkui.

119
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,970
I will keep that retreat order for you.

120
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,960
But I can't give it to you now.

121
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,180
I got the test results.

122
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,640
Brain tumor.

123
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:51,130
The doctor said I have less than a year to live.

124
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,320
Or rather,

125
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:54,280
I won't make it out of the Xuzhou battlefield.

126
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:55,400
But don't worry.

127
00:07:56,159 --> 00:07:57,040
Before I die,

128
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,570
I will definitely send all the materials,

129
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,730
along with my handwritten testimony,

130
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,020
to the Ministry of War.

131
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,360
Go to Wuhan now.

132
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,440
Find your old father,

133
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:06,640
and wait for me there.

134
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,090
I'll distract them now.

135
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,520
Go quickly.

136
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:15,600
Lu Yun.

137
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:23,170
Maybe it's a misdiagnosis.

138
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:26,380
I'll wait for you in Wuhan.

139
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,240
This torn padded jacket of yours

140
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,770
doesn't match your vibe

141
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,520
at all.

142
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,200
Stop.

143
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:53,700
Seventy-five.

144
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:54,840
Good. Not bad.

145
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:57,340
All right, come report tomorrow.

146
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,480
Thank you. Thank you.

147
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:00,840
Next.

148
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:10,240
Have a seat.

149
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:19,970
Why aren't you sitting?

150
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:22,800
Sorry.

151
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,840
I don't know how.

152
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,200
You know how to use an abacus, right?

153
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,360
No.

154
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:35,490
Have you ever been a secretary?

155
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,320
No.

156
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,920
Do you have children?

157
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:47,480
Yes.

158
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,880
But I know English.

159
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:55,850
I can translate.

160
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:58,540
I am also good at bookkeeping.

161
00:10:58,920 --> 00:10:59,920
Next.

162
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:01,000
Please.

163
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,240
When I was in college,

164
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:04,200
my poems were published in the newspaper.

165
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:04,640
I'm sorry.

166
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:05,280
Next.

167
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,400
When I was in middle school,

168
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:07,960
I participated in a speech contest.

169
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:09,120
I won first place.

170
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,200
You can sit there.

171
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,160
Sir.

172
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,720
I can do the cleaning.

173
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:14,200
I can do the laundry.

174
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:17,320
I've also made duck blood and vermicelli soup.

175
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:19,600
Sir.

176
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,240
I can learn.

177
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,520
I... I can learn to type.

178
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:26,840
Really.

179
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:29,880
I've always been a fast learner.

180
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,320
I can also type 75 words.

181
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,440
80... I can also do 85.

182
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:35,800
I can do it.

183
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:37,560
I can do it. Believe me.

184
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,360
What do you think?

185
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,840
Madam, our shop is closed.

186
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:24,240
Excuse me.

187
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,360
Is there a master named Meng

188
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:27,280
in your shop?

189
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,760
Named Meng?

190
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,120
Meng Wanfu.

191
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:33,040
Yes.

192
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:36,200
I'll say it again.

193
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:37,680
If you take the house back

194
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:38,880
and collect the rent,

195
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:41,140
you wouldn't need to go out to work at all.

196
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:45,660
I originally counted on my old friends in Shanghai.

197
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,200
But unexpectedly,

198
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,200
either I couldn't find them,

199
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:51,280
or when I finally contacted them,

200
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:54,520
they were hesitant and couldn't even take care of themselves.

201
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:55,480
I really didn't know

202
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,720
that finding a suitable job

203
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:57,980
would be so difficult.

204
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:05,720
Here.

205
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:08,440
This is egg tea from my hometown.

206
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:09,960
It clears internal heat.

207
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:12,620
Stir it with chopsticks. There's sugar inside.

208
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,360
Is it good?

209
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:31,840
It smells good.

210
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:44,410
I've been having nightmares these past two days.

211
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,880
I always dream about

212
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,360
that mother and her four sons.

213
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:50,940
Then I wake up in a cold sweat from fright.

214
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:52,600
After waking up,

215
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:55,120
looking at Yueming sleeping beside me,

216
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:58,400
I break out in a cold sweat again out of lingering fear.

217
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,200
Yes.

218
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:01,280
No matter how tragic,

219
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:03,720
it couldn't be more tragic than that day.

220
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,880
So, what does this current hardship

221
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,200
even count for?

222
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,560
Let's not lose heart.

223
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,200
I'm not losing heart.

224
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,060
And I wouldn't dare to either.

225
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:14,800
Your brigade commander hasn't been found yet.

226
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,440
Grandpa and the children

227
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:18,040
also rely on me to hold up.

228
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,400
If I can't hold up,

229
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:20,560
what will they do?

230
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:24,520
Don't they say things will sort themselves out in the end?

231
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,200
Since we're alive,

232
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,610
we must have hope in our hearts.

233
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:30,090
As long as there is hope,

234
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:31,300
we can keep living.

235
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:33,000
That's right.

236
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:38,520
Did you send the letter to Xiaoyue?

237
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,480
I sent it.

238
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:42,600
What kind of girl is she?

239
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,600
Is she cute and gentle?

240
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:47,600
Gentle?

241
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,640
Our Xiaoyue

242
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:50,840
in her whole life.

243
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:52,120
She wants to know gentleness,

244
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:53,980
but gentleness doesn't know her.

245
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,480
She's quite fierce.

246
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:57,970
I remember one time,

247
00:14:58,520 --> 00:14:59,280
Miss Yu,

248
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:01,120
her master,

249
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:02,640
took her to that...

250
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:04,260
something 'dern'.

251
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:05,440
Modern.

252
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:07,800
You put wires in your hair,

253
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,560
turn on the electricity,

254
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:10,640
and the hair becomes curly.

255
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:11,900
She ran back to show me.

256
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:13,040
I was so mad.

257
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:13,880
I said,

258
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,440
'Doesn't it look like a chicken's butt?'

259
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:16,640
Before I could finish,

260
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:17,900
a powerful palm strike

261
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,720
hit me on the back.

262
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,480
It hurt so much!

263
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,320
But a moment later,

264
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,440
she felt sorry for me.

265
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,640
She searched everywhere for badger oil

266
00:15:27,640 --> 00:15:28,840
and applied the medicine for me.

267
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,560
When she was applying the medicine,

268
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:31,440
I told her,

269
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:34,080
'If you don't hit me in the future,

270
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,760
you won't have to treat me, right?'

271
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:36,760
Guess what she said?

272
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:37,560
'No way.'

273
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:40,250
'I have to hit you, and I have to treat you.'

274
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,760
She said exactly the same thing as you.

275
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:43,840
You women are,

276
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:45,440
aren't you?

277
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:55,520
Go to hell.

278
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:07,280
Although our Xiaoyue is heavy-handed,

279
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,240
she is very skillful.

280
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:11,540
I'll show you something good.

281
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,160
Look.

282
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:19,640
This was embroidered by Xiaoyue herself.

283
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:22,280
It's called 'Clouds Covering the Moon'.

284
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:23,880
Well embroidered, isn't it?

285
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:27,000
It's called 'Clouds Chasing the Moon'.

286
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:28,520
Chasing the Moon?

287
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:29,960
Chasing.

288
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:32,690
Chasing the Moon is better.

289
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,360
Chasing is better than covering.

290
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,960
Covering means blocking it.

291
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,200
Chasing is good.

292
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:38,680
Clouds Chasing the Moon.

293
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:39,480
I remember

294
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,920
when she gave me this

295
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,480
in the barracks,

296
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:44,620
she just stuffed it into my hands.

297
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:46,490
I didn't notice it then.

298
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:47,720
I just smelled

299
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:49,040
it had Xiaoyue's

300
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:50,680
osmanthus hair oil scent.

301
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,140
It smelled so good.

302
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:53,240
When I opened it,

303
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:55,560
there was 35.80 yuan inside.

304
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:57,700
It was all the private savings

305
00:16:58,480 --> 00:17:00,480
she had accumulated over the years.

306
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,440
She is so nice.

307
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:04,040
So when I have money in the future,

308
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,599
I will pay her back ten, a hundred,

309
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,960
or a thousand times over.

310
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:52,560
No.

311
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:55,580
Isn't this your travel expense to Wuhan?

312
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,200
Now you have to take a plane to Wuhan.

313
00:17:58,760 --> 00:18:00,820
It will take forever to save up for it.

314
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,440
It's nothing.

315
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:05,000
You don't even have money to buy rice, do you?

316
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,600
Master and the child

317
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:09,200
can't go hungry.

318
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:19,700
Even if you have money now,

319
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:21,280
you can't buy rice.

320
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:24,240
Rice shops are rationing.

321
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:25,960
I went to line up.

322
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:28,480
There's just a hole in the wooden board.

323
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:31,160
The people in line are outside,

324
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:34,020
and they can't see what it looks like inside.

325
00:18:34,920 --> 00:18:36,320
I waited for three hours,

326
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:37,760
and before it was my turn,

327
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,400
the shop closed.

328
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:42,320
Wanfu.

329
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:46,500
I came to see you today,

330
00:18:46,680 --> 00:18:48,280
not to borrow money from you.

331
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:54,960
Aren't you a cook at the restaurant?

332
00:18:55,480 --> 00:18:56,480
I was wondering

333
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,730
if I could borrow some rice from your restaurant.

334
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,000
Not a lot.

335
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:04,580
Just enough for a few days.

336
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:06,440
When I find a job,

337
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:08,500
I'll definitely pay you back.

338
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:19,120
Madam, let me tell you the truth.

339
00:19:20,840 --> 00:19:21,960
Our shop

340
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:24,250
doesn't have much rice either.

341
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,410
And our manager is very shrewd,

342
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:28,280
he calculates very clearly.

343
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:30,480
He wishes he could live in the rice vat every day.

344
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:31,720
It's not his fault.

345
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,660
The whole concession is short of rice recently.

346
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:36,120
I heard

347
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,720
that the Japanese have designated the rice supplying Shanghai

348
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:40,520
all as military rice areas.

349
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:43,120
Now the concession can only rely on foreign rice,

350
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,600
but the ships carrying foreign rice

351
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,040
are stopped by the Japanese on the river

352
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,240
and are not allowed to enter.

353
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:48,840
So the rice in the concession

354
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:50,160
can only get less and less,

355
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:51,760
and more and more expensive.

356
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:53,920
How about this.

357
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:56,360
Our manager was just telling me today

358
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:58,960
that he wants to go to West Shanghai tomorrow

359
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:00,560
or Hongkou

360
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:02,440
to get some black market rice.

361
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,600
I'll go with him

362
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:05,740
to see if I can get some for you too.

363
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,480
Wanfu, you must not go.

364
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:09,280
That is an area occupied by the Japanese.

365
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:10,480
It's very dangerous.

366
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:12,370
The Japanese did it on purpose.

367
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:13,680
They want to strangle

368
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:14,600
the authorities of the concession,

369
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:16,760
forcing them to sign an agreement with the Japanese military

370
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:20,560
to make it easier for them to catch anti-Japanese elements in the concession.

371
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:21,760
If you run over there,

372
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:23,620
who knows if you can come back.

373
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:24,320
But,

374
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:26,120
we can't just starve, right?

375
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:28,360
We can't just sit and wait for death.

376
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:30,120
So,

377
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:32,810
money should be spent where it's needed most.

378
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:35,800
You hold this,

379
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:37,280
and you'll feel at ease.

380
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:46,320
Thank you, Wanfu.

381
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:48,560
I will definitely pay you back.

382
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:49,600
Okay.

383
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:54,400
Wanfu,

384
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:57,080
can I take the rest of the buns?

385
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,360
Absolutely.

386
00:20:58,480 --> 00:20:59,880
I saved some for Master too.

387
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:01,340
Wait a moment, right away.

388
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,840
These buns,

389
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:16,640
Master can eat them tonight,

390
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:17,840
and tomorrow morning,

391
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,240
you can steam them again,

392
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:22,140
and it'll be another meal.

393
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:24,800
I'll get you a

394
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:25,880
cloth bag later.

395
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:28,560
Thank you.

396
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:30,520
What's this?

397
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:31,840
Money for the buns.

398
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:32,970
I'm buying the buns.

399
00:21:34,120 --> 00:21:35,760
Ma'am, you are really interesting.

400
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,360
You take the money I lent you,

401
00:21:37,520 --> 00:21:39,360
and buy the buns I gave you.

402
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:41,520
What needs to be paid must be paid.

403
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:43,280
And for the egg tea too.

404
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:46,720
Ma'am,

405
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:49,360
It's normal to take a little extra.

406
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:51,480
Everyone has their own way.

407
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:52,610
It's normal.

408
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,320
No.

409
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:55,880
Business is business.

410
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,080
That's my principle.

411
00:21:58,160 --> 00:21:58,960
Right.

412
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:01,200
The Zhang family all share this principle.

413
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,930
It's Ding Yujiao's principle.

414
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,240
Okay.

415
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:06,280
How about this?

416
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:13,660
I'll treat this

417
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:16,360
as the money I lent you for the buns

418
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:17,520
and the egg tea.

419
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:18,880
As soon as you leave,

420
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,440
I'll put the money in the register.

421
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:21,120
Okay?

422
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:28,650
It's enough.

423
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:33,080
I'll pay you back everything later.

424
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,160
I'll be waiting.

425
00:22:39,480 --> 00:22:41,040
I'll wrap them up for you.

426
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:57,160
The crescent moon shines over several provinces.

427
00:22:57,920 --> 00:23:05,760
Some families are happy, some are sad.

428
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:13,720
Some couples share a bed curtain,

429
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:22,160
some are scattered in other provinces.

430
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,520
Brother Wanfu.

431
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:40,280
This is the first song

432
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:42,960
I taught you to sing after we met.

433
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,040
I sang it to you today.

434
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:47,200
Did you hear it?

435
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:02,000
I don't know if I did the right thing.

436
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:04,130
At that time, Brother Wanfu

437
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:06,560
buried my mother like this.

438
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:00,240
All right.

439
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:07,120
I don't want to see you wear a widow's bun anymore.

440
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:08,000
You've cried

441
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:09,320
and visited the grave.

442
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:10,600
Don't use this paper shackle

443
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:11,560
to bind your mind anymore.

444
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:11,840
Xiaoyue.

445
00:25:11,840 --> 00:25:12,900
What are you doing?

446
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:15,760
I still have to observe mourning for Brother Wanfu.

447
00:25:15,760 --> 00:25:16,600
Xiaoyue.

448
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:18,960
Wanfu is an anti-Japanese martyr.

449
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,040
This is just a cenotaph,

450
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:21,080
just a memory.

451
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:22,880
I think it's more important

452
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:25,040
to pay tribute and commemorate with your heart,

453
00:25:25,040 --> 00:25:26,570
rather than outward forms.

454
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:29,240
Xiaoyue, times have changed.

455
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,320
The war requires everyone to stand up

456
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:32,780
and take responsibility,

457
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:34,080
women included.

458
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:35,840
From now on,

459
00:25:36,480 --> 00:25:37,740
you are nobody's widow

460
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:39,680
and not my maid.

461
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:41,400
You are yourself,

462
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:42,960
Han Xiaoyue.

463
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:46,720
Miss, what do you mean?

464
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:48,800
You don't want me anymore?

465
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:50,240
No, silly girl.

466
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:52,000
You used to be my maid.

467
00:25:52,240 --> 00:25:55,200
From now on, you are nobody's maid,

468
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:57,930
and you don't have to depend on anyone.

469
00:25:58,080 --> 00:26:01,080
You've confused me.

470
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:02,600
Let me tell you.

471
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,600
Being a maid is just a job.

472
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:07,000
You can have an independent personality,

473
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,040
ideals,

474
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:09,720
and thoughts.

475
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:11,840
This is the real Han Xiaoyue.

476
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,360
I still don't understand

477
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:15,720
what you mean.

478
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:19,240
Being a nurse

479
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:21,000
to save everyone's life.

480
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:22,720
Zuliang, I've decided

481
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:23,840
to take Xiaoyue with me

482
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:25,700
to join the nurse training class.

483
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:27,770
It's decided, Xiaoyue.

484
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:31,560
You just taught someone to be independent,

485
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:33,890
and now you're making decisions for them.

486
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,200
Are you willing to go?

487
00:26:39,280 --> 00:26:41,010
I will go wherever you go, Miss.

488
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,240
Does this count as having an independent thought?

489
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:45,400
I guess.

490
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:47,560
Zuliang,

491
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:48,600
I'm serious.

492
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:50,640
Last time I just wasn't prepared.

493
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:51,280
This time,

494
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:53,440
you can assign the hardest and most tiring tasks

495
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:54,040
to Xiaoyue and me.

496
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:55,920
This time won't be easier than the last,

497
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:58,040
and it will be even harder and more tiring.

498
00:26:58,040 --> 00:26:59,040
Can you handle it?

499
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:00,920
Learning from the mistakes of last time,

500
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:01,760
I will definitely do better.

501
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:04,120
Don't forget you faint at the sight of blood.

502
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:06,180
I can't possibly faint a second time.

503
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:18,900
Brother Wanfu.

504
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:22,200
I will be fine.

505
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:32,160
Miss, wait for me!

506
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:41,400
So, after all this time fighting in the War of Resistance,

507
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:43,480
have we gained nothing?

508
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:47,240
Our answer is no.

509
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:49,650
On December 31st last year,

510
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:50,980
Comrade Zhou Enlai

511
00:27:51,320 --> 00:27:53,200
delivered a speech at Wuhan University titled

512
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:55,560
'The Nature

513
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:56,360
and Tasks

514
00:27:56,360 --> 00:27:58,000
of the Youth Movement at the Present Stage'.

515
00:27:58,000 --> 00:27:58,960
In this speech,

516
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:00,720
Comrade Zhou Enlai mentioned that

517
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:01,960
this War of Resistance

518
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:03,960
has given our Chinese nation

519
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:07,880
unprecedented valuable experience

520
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:08,970
and lessons.

521
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:11,400
This War of Resistance is sacred

522
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:13,280
because through this war,

523
00:28:13,520 --> 00:28:15,240
our Chinese nation

524
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:18,920
has stood up in the world

525
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:22,840
and strongly united against foreign enemies.

526
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:27,760
Under the unified will of the entire nation,

527
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:31,330
the freedom to resist Japan can also be achieved.

528
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:33,840
But compared to the Japanese,

529
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:35,760
we were completely unprepared,

530
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:37,520
had subjective flaws,

531
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:39,720
and strategic and tactical errors

532
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:41,920
were also unavoidable.

533
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:44,360
We indeed suffered setbacks.

534
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:46,240
But will these setbacks

535
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:48,560
determine the final outcome

536
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,080
of the Sino-Japanese War?

537
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:51,680
No.

538
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,080
No!

539
00:28:58,040 --> 00:28:59,080
Up until now,

540
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:00,800
national mobilization

541
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:03,760
has not yet been effectively implemented.

542
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:06,920
So the moment that decides the outcome

543
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:09,560
will be in the

544
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:11,570
last minute of our protracted war.

545
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:15,720
As Comrade Zhou Enlai advocated,

546
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:17,700
the vast numbers of youth,

547
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:20,840
not only must you, in the cause of national salvation,

548
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:22,700
revive the nation from its peril,

549
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,060
but also in the future,

550
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:26,800
bear the responsibility of nation-building.

551
00:29:27,080 --> 00:29:28,320
Go to the army,

552
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,530
go to the battlefield service,

553
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:31,940
go to the countryside,

554
00:29:32,440 --> 00:29:35,680
and go to the areas occupied by the enemy.

555
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:37,440
Good!

556
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:55,560
Revive the nation, resist the Japanese invaders.

557
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:58,040
Revive the nation, resist the Japanese invaders.

558
00:29:58,040 --> 00:30:00,280
Revive the nation, resist the Japanese invaders.

559
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:02,560
Revive the nation, resist the Japanese invaders.

560
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:04,760
Revive the nation, resist the Japanese invaders.

561
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:07,280
Revive the nation, resist the Japanese invaders.

562
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:08,160
Kill!

563
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:10,280
Kill!

564
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:13,560
Kill!

565
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:21,640
Kill!

566
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:27,080
Brother Kong.

567
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:31,640
Brother Kong.

568
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:33,200
Brother Kong.

569
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:34,200
Zhou.

570
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:36,840
They all said you left, Brother Kong.

571
00:30:37,120 --> 00:30:38,120
I'm back now, aren't I?

572
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:39,080
Brother Kong.

573
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,280
Where are Platoon Leader You and the others?

574
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:43,600
Platoon Leader You had an argument with the company commander this morning.

575
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:44,240
Why?

576
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:45,800
Over the uniforms and equipment.

577
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:47,440
We don't even have food to eat now.

578
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:47,880
They said

579
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:49,880
they were going to borrow some from the Northwest Army's uniform depot.

580
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:51,140
That's not borrowing.

581
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:52,760
Do you know where the uniform depot is?

582
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:53,200
I know.

583
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:53,920
Take me there.

584
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:54,400
Okay.

585
00:31:16,800 --> 00:31:17,860
What are you doing?

586
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,530
Help me catch this chicken.

587
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:21,360
Quick.

588
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:22,200
Help me.

589
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:23,330
Help me. Come on.

590
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:24,520
Give me a hand.

591
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:25,980
Come on. Give me a hand.

592
00:31:26,320 --> 00:31:27,120
This chicken.

593
00:31:41,280 --> 00:31:42,120
Don't yell.

594
00:31:43,560 --> 00:31:44,400
Let me go.

595
00:31:50,600 --> 00:31:53,200
Don't yell. Thanks for your trouble, brother.

596
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:54,400
Hurry.

597
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:03,160
My God.

598
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,540
What kind of life are they living?

599
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:08,760
Great.

600
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:11,800
Food.

601
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:12,480
Food.

602
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:13,440
Give me a bite.

603
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:14,420
Don't waste it.

604
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:17,280
Crispy and tasty.

605
00:32:17,800 --> 00:32:19,200
Don't spill the food.

606
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,120
These are good stuff.

607
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:36,640
Brother, come here quickly.

608
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,160
Hurry.

609
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:38,680
There's good stuff here.

610
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:40,200
Put it down.

611
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:41,640
Why are you lifting this thing?

612
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:42,920
It's inconvenient to carry on the way back.

613
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,200
Just grab a rifle each.

614
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:45,800
Over there. Take that.

615
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:47,160
Platoon Leader, this is great.

616
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:48,160
This is good.

617
00:32:48,320 --> 00:32:49,050
Give it to me.

618
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:50,120
Let's go.

619
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:52,080
Hurry. Let's go.

620
00:32:53,440 --> 00:32:54,440
Why are you here?

621
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:56,080
Put the guns down.

622
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:56,800
Why put them down?

623
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:57,800
Do you want to die?

624
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:59,280
I borrowed them, okay?

625
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:00,960
Borrowed? Put them down.

626
00:33:00,960 --> 00:33:02,000
Give it to me.

627
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:04,280
Put down all the guns you took. Hurry up.

628
00:33:04,280 --> 00:33:04,880
Don't leave empty-handed.

629
00:33:04,880 --> 00:33:05,280
Put it down.

630
00:33:05,280 --> 00:33:06,080
Hurry up and go.

631
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:07,010
Let go. Let's go.

632
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:07,760
Don't leave empty-handed.

633
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:08,520
Let's go.

634
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:10,850
Don't leave empty-handed.

635
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:11,880
Let's go.

636
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:14,240
Go!

637
00:33:21,400 --> 00:33:22,200
Old You.

638
00:33:24,840 --> 00:33:25,720
I'm sorry.

639
00:33:32,120 --> 00:33:32,760
Quick,

640
00:33:33,120 --> 00:33:34,000
let's go.

641
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:34,840
Hurry up!

642
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:50,920
Mis... misunderstanding.

643
00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:52,400
Put all the guns down.

644
00:34:03,760 --> 00:34:04,880
Put the guns down.

645
00:34:05,560 --> 00:34:06,560
Put the guns down.

646
00:34:07,080 --> 00:34:08,080
Put them down.

647
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:10,679
Everyone, put them down.

648
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,280
Uncle,

649
00:34:30,239 --> 00:34:31,000
I'm back.

650
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:34,960
Your handwriting has greatly improved.

651
00:34:34,960 --> 00:34:36,489
You never stop practicing.

652
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:39,840
Yan Zhenqing's 'Draft of a Requiem to My Nephew',

653
00:34:40,199 --> 00:34:41,880
every word goes straight to my heart.

654
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:42,679
That's great.

655
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:44,699
It's a pity there's no rice paper,

656
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:47,280
so I can only scribble on newspapers.

657
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:50,130
Here are the newspapers you asked for.

658
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:57,520
Look at what's written here.

659
00:34:58,440 --> 00:35:01,920
Li Zongren personally led 100,000 strong men

660
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:03,400
to set up defenses in Sishui.

661
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:05,400
Good.

662
00:35:05,680 --> 00:35:06,640
Li Zongren

663
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:09,800
is the Supreme Commander of the Fifth War Area.

664
00:35:10,080 --> 00:35:12,880
The situation in southern Shandong is excellent.

665
00:35:12,920 --> 00:35:14,320
The people are inspired.

666
00:35:14,760 --> 00:35:16,960
No, I just think...

667
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,160
What's that?

668
00:35:21,160 --> 00:35:22,000
These are flyers

669
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,280
they handed me on the street.

670
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:24,320
Let me see.

671
00:35:30,520 --> 00:35:32,650
If we don't fight the Japanese devils,

672
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:35,200
life will be hard in the future.

673
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:39,040
Good. The spirit of the people isn't dead.

674
00:35:39,320 --> 00:35:39,760
Good.

675
00:35:41,480 --> 00:35:42,000
Well,

676
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:43,730
I have a different opinion.

677
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:45,770
What's so good about it?

678
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:47,140
Patriotism with words

679
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:48,000
and slogans.

680
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:49,440
What's the point?

681
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:50,730
It's all empty talk,

682
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:52,320
and has no real meaning.

683
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:53,720
Even school kids can shout slogans.

684
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:55,000
Like this today, like that tomorrow.

685
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:55,880
What's the use?

686
00:35:57,960 --> 00:35:58,640
Uncle,

687
00:35:59,160 --> 00:36:01,240
People like us who are reluctant to sell government bonds

688
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:02,500
are the real patriots.

689
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:03,360
Not at all.

690
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:05,000
You're wrong.

691
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:06,480
You have no vision,

692
00:36:07,120 --> 00:36:10,320
and you've completely lost the style of our Zhang family.

693
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:11,600
Come,

694
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:13,040
sit down.

695
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,320
Listen to me.

696
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:18,880
Look,

697
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:22,800
these words were written by school kids.

698
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:24,850
The handwriting is sloppy,

699
00:36:24,880 --> 00:36:25,800
unstructured,

700
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:27,720
and completely lacks discipline.

701
00:36:27,720 --> 00:36:29,000
But through this paper,

702
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:30,240
I see their hearts.

703
00:36:30,640 --> 00:36:32,300
This is the will of the people.

704
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:35,540
When the people are united, they can move Mount Tai.

705
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:39,400
Driving out the Japanese invaders requires this very spirit.

706
00:36:39,400 --> 00:36:42,120
United as one, there is nothing to worry about.

707
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,600
Great-grandfather.

708
00:36:43,640 --> 00:36:44,800
You're so young,

709
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:47,000
but all you think about all day are stocks,

710
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:48,280
business,

711
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:49,440
and bonds.

712
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:50,760
No, Uncle.

713
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:52,410
Facing a formidable enemy.

714
00:36:52,760 --> 00:36:53,520
Yunqi,

715
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:56,640
I don't expect you to be like Yunkui

716
00:36:57,040 --> 00:36:58,200
and die in battle.

717
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:00,320
But,

718
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:03,040
no matter what you do,

719
00:37:03,600 --> 00:37:05,640
don't be unscrupulous.

720
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:08,320
Understand?

721
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,240
Understood.

722
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:26,360
Madam.

723
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:27,560
Did you hear that?

724
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:29,640
The master is scolding Zhang Yunqi.

725
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:31,340
He's tearing him a new one.

726
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:33,040
Don't tell me that.

727
00:37:33,320 --> 00:37:34,250
Come and teach me

728
00:37:34,640 --> 00:37:35,920
how to make something out of

729
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,520
these three cabbage leaves.

730
00:37:37,680 --> 00:37:38,560
Shred them,

731
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:39,600
dice them,

732
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:41,290
or marinate them first?

733
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:43,840
What can you make out of this?

734
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:45,000
You don't have oil,

735
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,120
and you don't have meat.

736
00:37:46,120 --> 00:37:48,240
Even Emperor Qianlong wouldn't know what to do.

737
00:37:48,240 --> 00:37:50,680
Besides, you eat cabbage for breakfast,

738
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:52,360
cabbage for lunch,

739
00:37:52,640 --> 00:37:53,770
cabbage for dinner,

740
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:55,680
and cabbage again tomorrow morning.

741
00:37:55,680 --> 00:37:57,120
You're turning into a rabbit.

742
00:37:57,120 --> 00:37:57,880
What's wrong with a rabbit?

743
00:37:57,880 --> 00:38:00,680
Even if we turn into crickets, we still have to eat.

744
00:38:02,840 --> 00:38:05,520
People have to live and eat.

745
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:08,120
If we don't eat rice for a meal,

746
00:38:08,880 --> 00:38:10,400
we'll starve.

747
00:38:38,160 --> 00:38:40,290
Where are you going to get so much rice?

748
00:38:41,040 --> 00:38:42,000
Wait.

749
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:44,760
It spilled.

750
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:47,360
Didn't I tell you?

751
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:48,400
Baozi and I

752
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:49,880
cut a hole in the wire fence

753
00:38:49,880 --> 00:38:50,880
of the concession

754
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:52,200
and sneaked into Nanshi.

755
00:38:52,200 --> 00:38:53,120
We finally

756
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:56,130
managed to buy rice from a Japanese rice shop.

757
00:38:57,000 --> 00:38:57,680
It was so close.

758
00:38:57,680 --> 00:38:59,880
On our way back, we were searched by the Japs.

759
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,080
They even touched me.

760
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:03,680
Could I let them touch me?

761
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:05,560
You are lucky

762
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:07,160
they didn't take your life.

763
00:39:07,160 --> 00:39:08,640
Didn't I tell you not to go

764
00:39:08,800 --> 00:39:10,000
to the Japanese area?

765
00:39:11,240 --> 00:39:12,500
Then what should we do?

766
00:39:12,760 --> 00:39:14,520
We can't just starve to death.

767
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:16,640
People have to eat.

768
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:18,200
I tell you,

769
00:39:18,640 --> 00:39:20,800
this rice is very precious.

770
00:39:21,200 --> 00:39:23,240
We risked our lives for it.

771
00:39:23,680 --> 00:39:24,680
Today,

772
00:39:25,040 --> 00:39:26,240
you will make Grandpa

773
00:39:26,240 --> 00:39:28,280
a delicious pot of rice.

774
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:32,040
I'm going to hear how Wazi gets scolded.

775
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:33,320
Come back.

776
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:36,480
Wash the rice.

777
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:45,280
If there's no rice, there's no rice.

778
00:39:45,520 --> 00:39:47,560
Why did you sneak through the wire fence?

779
00:39:47,560 --> 00:39:48,280
Okay.

780
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:49,880
I won't do it again.

781
00:39:50,320 --> 00:39:51,850
Next time I see a wire fence,

782
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:53,380
I'll just wade through it.

783
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:55,720
If I meet Japs searching me again,

784
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:57,560
I'll just kick them.

785
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:58,720
How dare they touch me.

786
00:39:58,720 --> 00:39:59,680
Touching my leg.

787
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:01,320
I'll kick them to death.

788
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:23,160
Grandpa.

789
00:40:23,440 --> 00:40:24,360
Time to eat.

790
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:29,060
Come see what we're eating today.

791
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:33,120
Grandpa, look.

792
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:34,440
Rice.

793
00:40:35,560 --> 00:40:37,440
This is a rare thing.

794
00:40:41,240 --> 00:40:42,900
Where are Yujiao and Yueming?

795
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:45,360
Madam will come down after Yueming is full.

796
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:45,960
Okay.

797
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:47,840
Then let Yunqi and his wife

798
00:40:48,040 --> 00:40:49,240
come down and join us.

799
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:51,960
Why call them?

800
00:40:52,120 --> 00:40:52,960
Don't worry.

801
00:40:52,960 --> 00:40:54,280
They eat very well.

802
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:56,420
Hurry and taste it.

803
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:05,720
Is it good?

804
00:41:07,040 --> 00:41:08,400
Rice is still the best.

805
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:10,160
Of course.

806
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:14,860
Where did it come from?

807
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:16,200
I bought it.

808
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:17,400
Bought it?

809
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:19,480
Black market?

810
00:41:20,440 --> 00:41:21,370
Very expensive?

811
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:24,360
Not expensive at all.

812
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:26,720
I tell you.

813
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:29,720
Today, Baozi from our restaurant and I

814
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:32,800
sneaked through a hole to Nanshi to buy it.

815
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:35,360
The hole was so small,

816
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:36,820
it almost tore my clothes.

817
00:41:36,960 --> 00:41:37,960
When we came back,

818
00:41:37,960 --> 00:41:39,840
we were stopped by Japanese soldiers.

819
00:41:39,840 --> 00:41:41,570
They didn't find the rice on us.

820
00:41:41,600 --> 00:41:43,000
Do you know where I hid it?

821
00:41:44,320 --> 00:41:46,160
Look, I hid it in my trouser legs.

822
00:41:47,320 --> 00:41:48,780
Not a single grain leaked.

823
00:41:49,400 --> 00:41:50,660
Grandpa, don't worry.

824
00:41:50,920 --> 00:41:52,520
I washed this rice three times.

825
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:54,000
It's very clean, eat it.

826
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:56,800
It was Nanshi.

827
00:41:57,880 --> 00:41:58,720
Nanshi.

828
00:41:58,960 --> 00:42:00,440
A Japanese rice shop.

829
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:02,360
In all of Shanghai right now,

830
00:42:02,360 --> 00:42:03,690
rice is cheapest there.

831
00:42:10,840 --> 00:42:12,440
How can you eat this rice?

832
00:42:12,840 --> 00:42:14,240
What's wrong with this rice?

833
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:16,300
Didn't you just say it was delicious?

834
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:19,320
The thirsty do not drink from the Robber Spring.

835
00:42:19,640 --> 00:42:22,120
The hot do not rest in the shade of evil trees.

836
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,520
If you eat rice from this Japanese shop,

837
00:42:24,520 --> 00:42:25,960
you are willingly becoming

838
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:27,960
obedient subjects of the Japanese.

839
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:29,640
Master,

840
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:33,380
do you think I wanted to crawl through that hole?

841
00:42:33,560 --> 00:42:34,360
Do you think I wanted

842
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:36,160
to buy rice from a Japanese shop?

843
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:38,020
It's because we have no money.

844
00:42:38,120 --> 00:42:39,240
Come, sit.

845
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:45,680
Bo Yi and Shu Qi righteously refused to eat Zhou grain.

846
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:47,400
They picked ferns to eat,

847
00:42:47,680 --> 00:42:49,680
and eventually starved to death.

848
00:42:50,400 --> 00:42:52,720
You're saying things I don't understand again.

849
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:54,720
People of lofty ideals in China

850
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,600
uphold their integrity.

851
00:42:57,000 --> 00:43:00,130
They would rather go to Shouyang Mountain to pick ferns,

852
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:02,400
than eat Zhou grain,

853
00:43:02,720 --> 00:43:04,120
proving their will with death.
